---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 25, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'support@pixanovalabs.com';
---

<Layout
  title="Click to Censor Privacy Policy"
  description="How the Click to Censor browser extension handles your data. Your censor selections stay on your device, and the only data sent off-device is a license key to verify a premium purchase."
>
  <section class="policy">
    <div class="container policy__inner">
      <header class="policy__head">
        <div class="label">Legal</div>
        <h1 class="policy__title">Privacy Policy for Click to Censor</h1>
        <p class="policy__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="policy__intro card">
        <p>
          Click to Censor ("the extension", "we", "us", "our") is developed by
          <strong>Pixa Nova Labs</strong>. This policy explains what information the extension
          handles, why, and your choices. We have tried to keep it in plain language.
        </p>
        <p>
          In short: everything you censor stays on your own device. The extension has no analytics,
          no tracking, and no account. The only time any data leaves your device is when you choose
          to activate a premium license, in which case your license key is sent to our payment
          provider to confirm the purchase. We do not sell your data and we do not use it for
          advertising.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy__body">
        <h2>1. Information the extension handles</h2>
        <h3>Things stored only on your device (never uploaded to us)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Your censors.</strong> For each website, the extension saves the elements you
            chose to censor (as CSS selectors) and the style you picked (blur, blackout, or hide).
            This is stored locally in your browser so your censors persist across page reloads. It
            is never uploaded to us.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your premium status.</strong> If you activate a premium license, the extension
            stores a flag and your license key locally so it knows the paid features are unlocked.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Things sent off your device only when you use a feature</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Your license key (only if you buy and activate premium).</strong>
            When you enter a license key to unlock premium, the extension sends that key to our
            payment provider, Polar, to confirm it is valid. The extension also re-checks the key
            with Polar about once a day so that a refunded or disabled key stops unlocking the paid
            features. The key is the only thing sent, and only for this validation. If you never buy
            premium, no license key exists and nothing is ever sent.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What we do NOT collect</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The pages you visit, their content, or the elements you censor. These never leave your device.</li>
          <li>Your name, email, or any account. The extension has no sign-in.</li>
          <li>We do not use third-party advertising.</li>
          <li>We do not use third-party analytics or tracking.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How we use the information</h2>
        <p>
          The censors you create are used only to apply the blur, blackout, or hide styles you
          asked for, on your own device. Your license key is used only to verify a premium purchase.
          That's it. We do not sell your information, and we do not use it for advertising or
          profiling.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Service providers we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Polar</strong>: processes premium purchases and validates license keys. Your
            license key is sent to Polar only to confirm it is valid.
            (<a href="https://polar.sh/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polar Privacy Policy</a>)
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Permissions the extension asks for</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Access to the sites you visit (host permissions):</strong> needed so the
            extension can apply your censors on whatever page you choose to use it on. It only acts
            on the page when you ask it to.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Storage:</strong> needed to save your censors and premium status locally on your
            device.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Active tab:</strong> needed to start element-selection mode on the page you are
            currently viewing when you click the toolbar button.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Alarms:</strong> needed to re-check your premium license about once a day in the
            background.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>On your device:</strong> your censors and premium status stay until you remove
            them, clear the extension's data, or uninstall the extension.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>With our payment provider:</strong> we do not keep a separate copy of your
            license key. Polar holds purchase and license records under its own privacy terms.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Security</h2>
        <p>
          License validation between the extension and our payment provider is encrypted in transit
          using HTTPS.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Click to Censor is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
          personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your choices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can remove any censor at any time from the extension popup, or clear them all.</li>
          <li>You can remove all locally stored data by clearing the extension's data or uninstalling it.</li>
          <li>You can contact us with any privacy question using the details below.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy as the extension changes. When we do, we will update the "Last
          updated" date above. Significant changes will be reflected in the extension's store
          listing.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this policy, contact us at:
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy {
    padding-block: var(--space-16) var(--space-20);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .policy__inner {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .policy__head {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .policy__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--size-h1);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    line-height: var(--lh-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .policy__updated {
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy__intro {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    background-color: var(--color-neutral);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
  }

  .policy__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--size-h2);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .policy__body h3 {
    font-size: var(--size-h3);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy__body p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy__body ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .policy__body li {
    line-height: var(--lh-body);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy__body a {
    color: var(--color-tertiary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .policy__body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
</style>
